## CSS Class Naming Conventions

### Grid System (ALWAYS use this pattern)
```html
<div class="container">
    <div class="grid">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">Content</div>
    </div>
</div>
```
- Container: `.container` (centers content, adds padding)
- Grid: `.grid` (12-column grid system)
- Columns: `.col-12`, `.col-6`, `.col-3`, `.col-2`, `.col-1` (base classes activate at md breakpoint)
- Responsive: `.col-xs-*`, `.col-sm-*`, `.col-md-*`, `.col-lg-*`, `.col-xl-*`, `.col-xxl-*`, `.col-xxxl-*`

### Spacing Utilities (USE THESE - NO inline styles)
- Margin: `.mt-1` through `.mt-8`, `.mb-*`, `.ml-*`, `.mr-*`
- Padding: `.pt-*`, `.pb-*`, `.pl-*`, `.pr-*`, `.py-*` (vertical), `.px-*` (horizontal)
- NEVER use `style="padding: ..."` or `style="margin: ..."` - use utility classes

