## JavaScript Components (from components.js)

### Tabs Component
```html
<div class="tabs">
    <div class="tablist" role="tablist" aria-label="Tab navigation">
        <button class="tab is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tab-panel-1" id="tab-btn-1">Tab 1</button>
        <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tab-panel-2" id="tab-btn-2">Tab 2</button>
    </div>
    <div id="tab-panel-1" class="tab__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-btn-1">Content 1</div>
    <div id="tab-panel-2" class="tab__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-btn-2">Content 2</div>
</div>
```
- Requires: `utils.js (safeQuery, safeQueryAll)`
- Required attributes: role="tab" on buttons, role="tabpanel" on panels, aria-controls on tab buttons (must match panel id), aria-labelledby on panels (must match tab button id), aria-selected on tab buttons (true/false), .is-active class on active tab and panel

### Accordion Component
```html
<div class="accordion">
    <div class="accordion__item">
        <button class="accordion__button" aria-expanded="false">Question</button>
        <div class="accordion__panel" hidden>Answer</div>
    </div>
</div>
```
- Requires: `utils.js (safeQuery, safeQueryAll)`
- Required attributes: aria-expanded on buttons (true/false), hidden attribute on panels when closed

### Modal Component
```html
<!-- Trigger Button -->
<button data-modal-target="#my-modal">Open Modal</button>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal" id="my-modal" hidden>
    <div class="modal__overlay"></div>
    <div class="modal__dialog">
        <button data-modal-close aria-label="Close modal">Close</button>
        <h2>Modal Title</h2>
        <p>Modal content goes here</p>
    </div>
</div>
```
- Requires: `utils.js (safeQuery, safeQueryAll)`
- Data attributes: data-modal-target="#modal-id" - Trigger button attribute, data-modal-close - Close button attribute (can be multiple)
- Required structure: .modal container with id and hidden attribute, .modal__overlay for backdrop, .modal__dialog for content container

### Tooltip Component
```html
<button data-tooltip="Tooltip text here">Hover me</button>
```
- Requires: `None (standalone)`

### Code Copy Button
```html
<!-- Option 1: Pre/Code Block -->
<pre class="code-block">
    <code>const example = 'code here';</code>
</pre>

<!-- Option 2: Div with Code Example -->
<div class="code-example">
    const example = 'code here';
</div>
```
- Requires: `utils.js (copyToClipboard function)`
- Supported classes: .code-block - Standard pre/code block, .code-example - Div-based code example

## Forbidden Patterns

### ❌ NEVER DO THIS:
- NO inline `style=""` attributes (use utility classes)
- NO hardcoded pixel values (use `--space-*` variables)
- NO duplicate IDs across pages
- NO custom colors (use `--color-*` variables)
- NO direct DOM manipulation without `safeQuery`/`safeQueryAll` from utils.js
- NO framework dependencies (keep vanilla JS)
- NO missing ARIA labels on interactive elements
- NO missing alt text on images

### ✅ ALWAYS DO THIS:
- Use CSS custom properties for all values
- Use utility classes for spacing
- Use BEM naming convention
- Include ARIA attributes for accessibility
- Test in both light and dark themes
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Include skip links for accessibility

## Color Guidelines
- Always check colors work on both light and dark themes
- Use CSS custom properties for theme-aware colors: `var(--color-primary)`, `var(--color-text)`, etc.
- Test contrast ratios for accessibility (WCAG AA minimum)
- Available colors: `--color-primary`, `--color-secondary`, `--color-accent`, `--color-success`, `--color-danger`, `--color-warning`, `--color-text`, `--color-text-muted`, `--color-bg`, `--color-surface`, `--color-border`

## Responsive Breakpoints
- xs: 300px
- sm: 600px
- md: 768px
- lg: 1024px
- xl: 1280px
- xxl: 1600px
- xxxl: 2400px

## Design Tokens Reference
- Spacing: `--space-1` (8px) through `--space-16` (128px)
- Typography: `--font-size-xs` through `--font-size-4xl`
- Borders: `--border-radius`, `--border-radius-sm`, `--border-radius-lg`
- Shadows: `--shadow-sm`, `--shadow-md`, `--shadow-lg`
- See `assets/css/framework-unified.css` for complete token list

## Component Sync
- Components are defined in `assets/js/components.js`
- Always check components.js for latest component patterns
- Run `npm run sync-components` to update documentation from components.js

